Doc: A type defining the content model for a human-readable notification to the users of a service.

Source.Contents:
/#
   A type defining the content model for a human-readable notification to the users of a service.
 #/
record FpML5.reporting.ServiceAdvisory {
  # The category or type of the notification message, e.g. availability, product coverage, rules, etc.
  category : string?

  # A human-readable notification.
  description : string?

  # The time at which the information supplied by the advisory becomes effective. For example, if the advisory advises of a newly planned service outage, it will be the time the service outage begins.
  effectiveFrom : datetime?

  # The time at which the information supplied by the advisory becomes no longer effective. For example, if the advisory advises of a newly planned service outage, it will be the time the service outage ends.
  effectiveTo : datetime?

}

category.Doc: The category or type of the notification message, e.g. availability, product coverage, rules, etc.
category.Name: category

effectiveFrom.Doc: The time at which the information supplied by the advisory becomes effective. For example, if the advisory advises of a newly planned service outage, it will be the time the service outage begins.
effectiveFrom.Name: effectiveFrom

effectiveTo.Doc: The time at which the information supplied by the advisory becomes no longer effective. For example, if the advisory advises of a newly planned service outage, it will be the time the service outage ends.
effectiveTo.Name: effectiveTo
